authors.name: Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children

items.description:
Author(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children Narrator(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children - Does your baby have a hard time falling asleep?

- Are you looking for peaceful, soothing music your baby can fall asleep to ...

-... but don't want to hear "Rock-a-Bye Baby" for the thousandth time?

Enjoy modern lullabies that will reliably soothe you and your baby gently to sleep. To fall asleep, children need to feel safe. The soothing sleep music composed especially for babies and their parents helps you create a snug, secure atmosphere.

The unique soundscapes (piano, keyboard, guitar) satisfy our human need for security and relaxation. They are based on scientific studies that demonstrate the positive effects of music on our sleeping habits. In combination with the music, you will also hear the sound of ocean waves gently lapping at the shore. Ocean sounds are well loved by babies as they simulate their pre-birth experience in the womb, which babies remember fondly. The sound of the waves comforts them and promotes even, harmonious breathing.

This premium audiobook contains:
Eleven unique sleep tracks with a running time of over 120 minutes, composed by certified music therapists and played at the same rhythm as the resting heart rate. In addition, there are comforting nature sounds that satisfy our human need for security and relaxation.

Can't wait to play the music? Then download it now!

**** NOTE: SEVERAL of the tracks on the audiobook are played briefly in the audio sample. ****

items.description:
Author(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children Narrator(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children - Does your baby have a hard time falling asleep?

- Are you looking for peaceful, soothing music your baby can fall asleep to ...

-... but don't want to hear "Rock-a-Bye Baby" for the thousandth time?

Enjoy modern lullabies that will reliably soothe you and your baby gently to sleep. To fall asleep, children need to feel safe. The soothing sleep music composed especially for babies and their parents helps you create a snug, secure atmosphere.

The unique soundscapes (piano, keyboard, guitar) satisfy our human need for security and relaxation. They are based on scientific studies that demonstrate the positive effects of music on our sleeping habits. In combination with the music, you will also hear the sound of ocean waves gently lapping at the shore. Ocean sounds are well loved by babies as they simulate their pre-birth experience in the womb, which babies remember fondly. The sound of the waves comforts them and promotes even, harmonious breathing.

This premium audiobook contains:
Eleven unique sleep tracks with a running time of over 120 minutes, composed by certified music therapists and played at the same rhythm as the resting heart rate. In addition, there are comforting nature sounds that satisfy our human need for security and relaxation.

Can't wait to play the music? Then download it now!

**** NOTE: SEVERAL of the tracks on the audiobook are played briefly in the audio sample. ****

items.description:
Author(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children Narrator(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children - Does your baby have a hard time falling asleep?

- Are you looking for peaceful, soothing music your baby can fall asleep to ...

-... but don't want to hear "Rock-a-Bye Baby" for the thousandth time?

Enjoy modern lullabies that will reliably soothe you and your baby gently to sleep. To fall asleep, children need to feel safe. The soothing sleep music composed especially for babies and their parents helps you create a snug, secure atmosphere.

The unique soundscapes (piano, keyboard, guitar) satisfy our human need for security and relaxation. They are based on scientific studies that demonstrate the positive effects of music on our sleeping habits. In combination with the music, you will also hear the sound of ocean waves gently lapping at the shore. Ocean sounds are well loved by babies as they simulate their pre-birth experience in the womb, which babies remember fondly. The sound of the waves comforts them and promotes even, harmonious breathing.

This premium audiobook contains:
Eleven unique sleep tracks with a running time of over 120 minutes, composed by certified music therapists and played at the same rhythm as the resting heart rate. In addition, there are comforting nature sounds that satisfy our human need for security and relaxation.

Can't wait to play the music? Then download it now!

**** NOTE: SEVERAL of the tracks on the audiobook are played briefly in the audio sample. ****

items.description:
Author(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children Narrator(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children - Does your baby have a hard time falling asleep?

- Are you looking for peaceful, soothing music your baby can fall asleep to ...

-... but don't want to hear "Rock-a-Bye Baby" for the thousandth time?

Enjoy modern lullabies that will reliably soothe you and your baby gently to sleep. To fall asleep, children need to feel safe. The soothing sleep music composed especially for babies and their parents helps you create a snug, secure atmosphere.

The unique soundscapes (piano, keyboard, guitar) satisfy our human need for security and relaxation. They are based on scientific studies that demonstrate the positive effects of music on our sleeping habits. In combination with the music, you will also hear the sound of ocean waves gently lapping at the shore. Ocean sounds are well loved by babies as they simulate their pre-birth experience in the womb, which babies remember fondly. The sound of the waves comforts them and promotes even, harmonious breathing.

This premium audiobook contains:
Eleven unique sleep tracks with a running time of over 120 minutes, composed by certified music therapists and played at the same rhythm as the resting heart rate. In addition, there are comforting nature sounds that satisfy our human need for security and relaxation.

Can't wait to play the music? Then download it now!

**** NOTE: SEVERAL of the tracks on the audiobook are played briefly in the audio sample. ****

items.description:
Author(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children Narrator(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children - Does your baby have a hard time falling asleep?

- Are you looking for peaceful, soothing music your baby can fall asleep to ...

-... but don't want to hear "Rock-a-Bye Baby" for the thousandth time?

Enjoy modern lullabies that will reliably soothe you and your baby gently to sleep. To fall asleep, children need to feel safe. The soothing sleep music composed especially for babies and their parents helps you create a snug, secure atmosphere.

The unique soundscapes (piano, keyboard, guitar) satisfy our human need for security and relaxation. They are based on scientific studies that demonstrate the positive effects of music on our sleeping habits. In combination with the music, you will also hear the sound of ocean waves gently lapping at the shore. Ocean sounds are well loved by babies as they simulate their pre-birth experience in the womb, which babies remember fondly. The sound of the waves comforts them and promotes even, harmonious breathing.

This premium audiobook contains:
Eleven unique sleep tracks with a running time of over 120 minutes, composed by certified music therapists and played at the same rhythm as the resting heart rate. In addition, there are comforting nature sounds that satisfy our human need for security and relaxation.

Can't wait to play the music? Then download it now!

**** NOTE: SEVERAL of the tracks on the audiobook are played briefly in the audio sample. ****

items.description:
Author(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children Narrator(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children - Does your baby have a hard time falling asleep?

- Are you looking for peaceful, soothing music your baby can fall asleep to ...

-... but don't want to hear "Rock-a-Bye Baby" for the thousandth time?

Enjoy modern lullabies that will reliably soothe you and your baby gently to sleep. To fall asleep, children need to feel safe. The soothing sleep music composed especially for babies and their parents helps you create a snug, secure atmosphere.

The unique soundscapes (piano, keyboard, guitar) satisfy our human need for security and relaxation. They are based on scientific studies that demonstrate the positive effects of music on our sleeping habits. In combination with the music, you will also hear the sound of ocean waves gently lapping at the shore. Ocean sounds are well loved by babies as they simulate their pre-birth experience in the womb, which babies remember fondly. The sound of the waves comforts them and promotes even, harmonious breathing.

This premium audiobook contains:
Eleven unique sleep tracks with a running time of over 120 minutes, composed by certified music therapists and played at the same rhythm as the resting heart rate. In addition, there are comforting nature sounds that satisfy our human need for security and relaxation.

Can't wait to play the music? Then download it now!

**** NOTE: SEVERAL of the tracks on the audiobook are played briefly in the audio sample. ****

Author(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children Narrator(s): Soothing Music for Babies and Small Children - Does your baby have a hard time falling asleep?

- Are you looking for peaceful, soothing music your baby can fall asleep to ...

-... but don't want to hear "Rock-a-Bye Baby" for the thousandth time?

Enjoy modern lullabies that will reliably soothe you and your baby gently to sleep. To fall asleep, children need to feel safe. The soothing sleep music composed especially for babies and their parents helps you create a snug, secure atmosphere.

The unique soundscapes (piano, keyboard, guitar) satisfy our human need for security and relaxation. They are based on scientific studies that demonstrate the positive effects of music on our sleeping habits. In combination with the music, you will also hear the sound of ocean waves gently lapping at the shore. Ocean sounds are well loved by babies as they simulate their pre-birth experience in the womb, which babies remember fondly. The sound of the waves comforts them and promotes even, harmonious breathing.

This premium audiobook contains:
Eleven unique sleep tracks with a running time of over 120 minutes, composed by certified music therapists and played at the same rhythm as the resting heart rate. In addition, there are comforting nature sounds that satisfy our human need for security and relaxation.

Can't wait to play the music? Then download it now!

**** NOTE: SEVERAL of the tracks on the audiobook are played briefly in the audio sample. ****

args.data: ### ウィキペディアは売り物ではありません。 **こんにちは。1分でいいので、どうか読み飛ばさないでください** 今日、私たちの非営利団体は、皆様のご支援をお願いいたします。あなたの支援は、とても大切なものです。ウィキペディアが設立された当初、無料で広告なしで学べる初めてのようなオンライン空間でした。このウェブサイトはあなたのものです。読者の僅か2%の方々しか寄付をされていませんが、できる範囲でのご支援をいただければ大変助かります。 — ウィキペディアとその姉妹サイトのホストであるウィキメディア財団より. [W 15] On February 9, 2014, _The New York Times_ reported that Wikipedia had 18 billion page views and nearly 500 million unique visitors a month, "according to the ratings firm comScore". "[57] When contacted on this matter, Clay Shirky, associate professor at New York University and fellow at Harv.... Anyone registered on the site can create an article for publication; registration is not required to edit articles. Similarly, because anyone can edit any article, the site's entries are vulnerable to unscrupulous edits. In August 2007, Virgil Griffiths created a site, WikiScanner, where users could.... Hosted by the Wikimedia Foundation, it consists of freely editable content, whose articles also have numerous links to guide readers towards more information. Since its creation on January 15, 2001, it has grown into the world's largest reference website, attracting over a billion visitors monthly. .... We provide this service in the pursuit of open knowledge that’s always ad-free and never tracks your data. If you have experience with Java and the Android SDK, then we look forward to your contributions! If you would like to disable this feature, press "Settings," then turn off "Send crash reports".... A typical wiki contains multiple pages that can either be edited by the public or limited to use within an organization for maintaining its internal knowledge base. Wikis can also make WYSIWYG editing available to users, usually through a JavaScript control that translates graphically entered format.... Being a user- funded effort means Wikipedia operates entirely on user donations and grants with the ultimate aim of bringing free knowledge to everyone. Anyone with internet access can change a Wikipedia page, which means that the information on pages isn't always reliable. The site also has a commu.... The shift from informal sharing of code to explicit open-source practice actually began a few years earlier with Richard M. Stallman. By 1991 Internet access had become sufficiently common that e-mail could knit together a large worldwide community of volunteer developers and function as an effectiv.... Wikipedia is a **free multilingual online encyclopedia collaboratively** created and maintained by **volunteer** editors. Thus, Wikipedia's value as a multilingual resource is increasing over time. Anyone can edit an article at any time, including you!

speak: ウィキペディアはオンラインにある無料の百科事典です。
